<subSubSection id="D7F56569FFF5FFE3DDB0D747E254860A" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9F5036E2FFF5FFE3DDB0D747E254860A" blockId="1.[151,1437,618,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="AD9BEAF0FFF5FFE3DDB0D747E21487B7" bold="true" box="[151,274,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
After 
<bibRefCitation id="FB7E4B13FFF5FFE3DC7BD746E14C87B6" author="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[348,586,619,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref3972" refString="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V. (2014) Water mites from Mount Kinabalu and the Crocker Range, Borneo, Malaysia (Acari: Hydrachnidia), with the description of 34 new species. Zootaxa, 3876 (1), 1 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3876.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Smit &amp; Pešić (2014)</bibRefCitation>
: Idiosoma with complete dorsal and ventral shield; dorsal furrow with one pair of lateroglandularia in shallow lateral indentations of the dorsal shield; three pairs of genital acetabula, Ac plates fused with the ventral shield in males but separate in females (
<figureCitation id="07D42A67FFF5FFE3DEAAD79EE0E887FE" box="[909,1006,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,185,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[253,1335,176,1914]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ljania jini sp. nov., male:A = dorsal view; B = ventral view; C = gnathosoma and chelicera; D = palp; E = I-L-3–6; F = II-L-1–6; G =III-L-2–6; H = IV- L-1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Figs. 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="07D42A67FFF5FFE3DEDED79EE71A87FE" box="[1017,1052,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[204,1380,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ljania jini sp. nov., female: A = dorsal view; B = ventral view; C = gnathosoma and chelicera; D = palp; E = I-L- 1–6; F = II-L-1–6; G =III-L-2–6; H = IV-L-1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761711/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="07D42A67FFF5FFE3D900D79EE74C87FE" box="[1063,1098,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[228,1359,192,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[219,1369,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ljania guangxiensis sp. nov., female:A = dorsal view; B = ventral view; C = I-L-1–6; D = II-L-1–6; E = III-L-1–6; F = IV-L-1–6; G = gnathosoma and chelicera; H = palp. Scale bars = 100 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">3B</figureCitation>
); a prominent ridge present on each side extending anterolaterally from insertions of IV-L; Posterolateral suture lines of Cx-IV maybe complete or completely absent; palp without projections or heavy ventral setae; Legs without sexual dimorphism, I-L obviously longer than II-L.
</paragraph>
